In &lt;691@mailrus.cc.umich.edu&gt; I wrote about turning 
	&lt;user at host&gt; =&gt; &lt;user@host&gt;
messed up mail to
	&lt;user@star.at.man.ac.uk&gt;.

If you have a sendmail ruleset that reads
	R$+ at $+	$1@$2

it would be a good idea to remove it.  Who generates "at"s
anymore, anyway?  

Thanks to Bill Wisner and Philip Prindeville for confirming
my intuition on this, and best of luck to everyone trying
to send mail to the astronomy dep't at Manchester.

--Ed

